---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';

const schema = {
  "@context": "https://schema.org",
  "@type": "WebApplication",
  "name": "Bitcoin Simulator",
  "url": "https://bitcoinsimulator.cowsandbytes.party/",
  "description": "Bitcoin simulator for blockchain courses. Supports multiple chains, mining, transactions, wallets and fork visualization.",
  "applicationCategory": "EducationalApplication",
  "operatingSystem": "Web",
  "author": {
    "@type": "Person",
    "name": "Marijn Bent",
    "url": "https://marijnbent.nl"
  },
  "offers": {
    "@type": "Offer",
    "price": "0",
    "priceCurrency": "EUR"
  }
};
---

<Layout
  title="Bitcoin simulator â€“ Marijn Bent"
  description="Bitcoin simulator for blockchain courses. Supports multiple chains, mining, transactions, wallets and fork visualization."
  schema={schema}
>
  <article class="prose-content">
    <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold tracking-tight mb-6">Bitcoin simulator</h1>

    <div class="space-y-4 text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed">
      <p>
        I give beginner blockchain courses a few times a year, mostly for people working in banking. The workshops are two days and cover both theory and hands-on work with Ethereum and Bitcoin. The problem is that the Bitcoin testnet has become hard to use - the tooling is clunky and confusing for beginners.
      </p>

      <p>
        I found an existing Bitcoin simulator online but the code was outdated, so I built my own over a weekend.
      </p>

      <p>
        It supports multiple blockchains, which works well for group exercises. You can visualize blocks, mine new ones, add transactions and send/receive coins with a built-in wallet. It also handles forks by displaying them and invalidating transactions that fall off the longest chain.
      </p>

      <p>
        Try it at <a href="https://bitcoinsimulator.cowsandbytes.party/" class="text-foreground font-medium underline underline-offset-4 hover:text-foreground/80 transition-colors">bitcoinsimulator.cowsandbytes.party</a>.
      </p>
    </div>
  </article>
</Layout>
